org.peertrust.tnviz.app
Class TNReplay

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Thread
      org.peertrust.tnviz.app.TNReplay
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Runnable
public class TNReplay
extends java.lang.Thread

The TNReplay class provides the means to visualize the sequence in which a graph was built. When activated, the class reads out the data from the given diagramm and highlights each node and edge one after another in the correct order in which they were created.

Constructor Detail

TNReplay

public TNReplay(TNGui gui,
                Graphics graphics,
                java.util.Vector graphPath)
Constructor for this class. In order to wirk correctly, the gui object, the graphics object and the graphPath are needed. The graphPath is a vector with the graph elements in the order in which they have been created.

Parameters:
gui - The gui object.
graphics - The graphics object.
graphPath - The graphPath with the graph elements.
Method Detail

run

public void run()
This method reads out the data from the graphPath and then highlights the graph elements on after another in the order in which they were created. Each node and edge will be highlighted by changing its color for 400 milliseconds. Only nodes which are not invisible will be highlighted. Invisible nodes will be ignored.
